Full Description: In 1996, Wayne Berry left Microsoft to start Sign Me Up Marketing in order to develop products and services that meet the needs of web developers who want to combine the efficiencies of database design without compromising the user experience. In 1998 another Microsoft expatriate, Dina Berry, joined Wayne in his efforts. Since day one the mission of the company has been to provide web developers and site owners with performance solutions that improve the visitor's experience. With an in-depth knowledge of website development CEO Wayne Berry clearly saw the writing on the wall - e-commerce, though growing rapidly, would face even greater challenges in the future unless one key issue was resolved. As the original founders and former editors of the web site 15 Seconds, they developed XBuilder in 1996 to meet the needs of web developers who wanted to combine the efficiencies of database design without compromising the user experience. In 2000, they introduced the much anticipated XCache to improve the performance and scalability of enterprise level dynamic web sites whose data changed frequently. Later in 2000, they introduced XTune to simplify web server performance optimization. The mission of the company is to provide web developers and site owners with performance solutions to improve site user experiences and scalability solutions to maximize web site uptime under stress.

Sun Phocus is the first and only company to use the patented HoloSun™ product in the building-integrated photovoltaics (BIPV) market.  Building-integrated photovoltaics (BIPV) are solar power-generating modules incorporated into the exterior surfaces of a building, serving a dual purpose as building material and electricity-generating device. Description: Spring Design Software
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: More than a spring calculator, ODOP:Spring is full-featured spring design software for engineering custom helical coil springs, including compression, torsion and extension springs. While certainly capable of analyzing the performance of an existing spring design, our open-source and free to use web app is at its best when used to develop solutions to difficult and highly constrained original design problems. Typical spring calculators perform design analysis, requiring users to make repeated inputs (independent variables of the design equations like wire diameter, coil diameter, number of coils and loads) until the desired outputs (dependent variables like deflections, stresses, weight, and estimated cycle life) are achieved.  On the other hand, ODOP:Spring performs design synthesis to invert the dependent / independent relationships of the design equations and perform constrained optimization. You input specific goals, and ODOP:Spring returns the variable values that best meet those goals.
